                    Section 2 - Course Introduction
1 - Course Introduction
Docker and Containers are likely to be a large part of all IT professionals future
This is a follow on to the Docker And Containers Big Picture course
  - You may need to do that first if you do not know what containers are
The course uses the Docker Version 1.12

                    
                    Section 3 - Installing Docker
1 - Module Intro
The module shows how to install docker
  - The course will explain some of the behind the scenes information
Docker has a multitude of installation options 
  - Multiple OS'es
  - Cloud Infrastructre
  - On Premises installation
  - Many different installation types
Things in the tech world change fast so some of the course maybe different
To install
  - Ensure hyper-v is installed/enabled
  - https://www.docker.com/docker-windows
  - Use the package to install and accept license agreement

2 - Docker For Windows
The version targeted in the course is Windows 10 64 bit
The pre-requisites
  - Windows 10 64 bit
  - As clean an installation as possible
  - The use cases are for testing dev and learning docker
  - Although it is for windows it runs on a hyper-v vm running linux
  - To check docker is installed, at the command line
    - docker version

